{An elderly citizen of Pickering {has vivid memories of times long past. {Here in an interview with a pupil of {this school,he recalls some of them:-}
The First World War
Mr. Roland Shields of Ampleforth was 15 when he joined the Scarborough Green Howards 50th Division.He was trained at Scarborough and later moved to Redcar.Before he moved to Redcar he saw Scarborough being bombed.He first saw action in France at Calais and later went to Ypres in Belguim.Whilst he was in the trenches he saw rats, frogs and gloworms.He helped to carry the shell shock victims to safety. He saw one man blast his own ankle so that he would be returned home.He was overseas for 14 months and although 91 he still recalls the memories.
